<p style="color: #000000;">Three local sellers of everything from dinner wear to curios said on Wednesday 14th May that ivory was no longer welcome on their shelves. Wing On Department Store said it would stop selling ivory products in July, while Yue Hwa Chinese Products Emporium said it stopped selling ivory on May 7th and Chinese Arts &amp; Crafts ( HK) Ltd. said it stopped in March.</p>
<p style="color: #000000;">The notices ‚Äî given in letters from the three companies released on Wednesday by conservation groups ‚Äî came just a day before Hong Kong plans to burn a 30-ton¬†stockpile¬†of seized elephant ivory. ¬†Their moves ‚Äúsend a clear message that the consumption of ivory is rapidly becoming taboo in Hong Kong society,‚Äù said Alex Hofford, director of Hong Kong for Elephants, a local lobby group.</p>
